definition: to pick/to pluck/to collect/to select/to choose/to gather

sentences.english: At the same time, the artificial populations should be expanded from seeds collected in years of high seed set.
sentences.chinese: 豐年應適時採種，就地育苗，擴大人工種羣。

sentences.english: In practice, seeds should not be stored dry but stratified on removal from the fruit.
sentences.chinese: 實踐上，種子不需要幹藏而是採種後即層積。

sentences.english: Progenies were produced by each mother tree with 19 male trees.
sentences.chinese: 平均每個採種母樹與19個父本產生子代。

sentences.english: Maintenance and selection of parent stocks.
sentences.chinese: 採種母體之選擇及維持。
